com.phunware.advertising

Class PwNativeAd

  • java.lang.Object
    • NativeAdImpl
      • com.phunware.advertising.PwNativeAd

  • public class PwNativeAd
extends NativeAdImpl
    Native ads are advertisments designed to fit naturally into your app's look and feel. Predefined ad features are provided which your app consumes in a template that follows your UI's theme.

    Simple example:

          PwNativeAd nativeAd = PwNativeAd.getInstance(this, "YOUR_NATIVE_ZONE_ID");
      nativeAd.load();
      String iconUrl = nativeAd.getIconUrl();
      // get image from URL and load into your view

      • load

        public void load()
        Fire off an asynchronous request to the server for an ad. Use isLoaded() or PwNativeAd.PwNativeAdListener to determine when an ad is loaded. This should only be called once. To request a new ad, you should create a new instance.

      • cancelLoad

        public void cancelLoad()
        Cancel request for an ad. If a listener has been set (see setListener(PwNativeAdListener)), this will cause PwNativeAd.PwNativeAdListener.nativeAdDidFail(PwNativeAd, String) to be called if an ad is currently loading. Nothing happens if an ad is not loading.
